  ABSTRACT = {
In this paper the results of a search for bilinear equations of the
type $P(D_x,D_t)F\cdot F = 0$, which have three-soliton solutions, are
presented. Polynomials up to order 8 have been studied.  In addition
to the previously known cases of KP, BKP, and DKP equations and their
reductions, a new polynomial $P = D_xD_t(D_x^2+\sqrt{3} D_xD_t + D_t^2) +
aD_x^2+ bD_xD_t + cD_t^2$ has been found. Its complete integrability
is not known, but it has three-soliton solutions. Infinite sequences
of models with linear dispersion manifolds have also been found, e.g.,
$P = D_x^MD_t^ND_y^P$, if some powers are odd, and $P =
D_x^MD_t^N(D_x^2 - 1)^P$, if $M$ and $N$ are odd.
},
