  JOURNAL = {  Stud. Appl. Math.},
  YEAR = 1985,
  VOLUME = 73,
  PAGES = {183-220},
  ABSTRACT = {
An explicit, analytical model is presented of finite-amplitude waves
in shallow water. The waves in question have two independent spatial
periods, in two independent horizontal directions. Both short-crested
and long-crested waves are available from the model. Every wave
pattern is an exact solution of the Kadomtsev-Petviashvili equation,
